rogel.io.fopl

Class Symbol

  • java.lang.Object
    • rogel.io.fopl.Symbol

  • public final class Symbol
extends java.lang.Object
    A Symbol is an object that represents. Everything expressed in FOPL is done in terms of Symbols. In this implementation, Symbols follow the Herbrand interpretation and are merely objects that represent String-based names. There is only one Symbol for any given name.

    The set of all Symbols that are declared during the execution of any FOPL program constitute that program's domain of discourse.

    Author:
    recardona
    See Also:
    https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herbrand_interpretation

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        a Symbol with the given name.

      • generateSymbol

        public static Symbol generateSymbol()
        Generates a new Symbol within the domain of discourse. The new Symbol is guaranteed to be unique, and will be of the form G{number}, where {number} is an integer.
        Returns:
        the newly generated Symbol.

      • generateSymbol

        public static Symbol generateSymbol(java.lang.String prefix)
        Generates a new Symbol within the domain of discourse. The new Symbol is guaranteed to be unique, and will be of the form {prefix}{number}, where {prefix} is the parameter String, and {number} is an integer.
        Parameters:
        prefix - The prefix of the Symbol to generate.
        Returns:
        the newly generated Symbol.
